+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JnscGhY59oJF8DhBgE4AtX","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have now read every single file in the codebase. Here is the complete analysis.\n\n---\n\n## Full Project Structure\n\n```\n/workspace/\n  .eslintrc.cjs                          # ESLint config\n  .gitignore                             # ignores node_modules/ and dist/\n  TASK.md                                # Task description\n  package.json                           # Project metadata and dependencies\n  package-lock.json                      # Lock file\n  tsconfig.json                          # TypeScript config\n  vitest.config.ts                       # Vitest config\n  src/\n    core/\n      index.ts                           # Barrel re-exports\n      types.ts                           # All interfaces (Plugin, BuildContext, etc.)\n      engine.ts                          # BuildEngine class with DAG plugin system\n      templates.ts                       # Default and List template factories\n    plugins/\n      .gitkeep                           # Empty placeholder directory\n  tests/\n    core.test.ts                         # 15 tests for core engine\n    plugins/\n      markdown-ext.test.ts               # 8 tests\n      asset-pipeline.test.ts             # 8 tests\n      syntax-highlight.test.ts           # 8 tests (but note: 7 \"it\" blocks -- I'll detail below)\n      taxonomy.test.ts                   # 8 tests\n      rss-feed.test.ts                   # 7 tests\n      search-index.test.ts              # 7 tests\n      sitemap.test.ts                    # 7 tests\n      dev-server.test.ts                 # 7 tests\n```\n\n---\n\n## 1. The Plugin Interface (`/workspace/src/core/types.ts`)\n\nThere are 6 interfaces defined:\n\n### `SiteConfig`\n```typescript\ninterface SiteConfig {\n  title: string;\n  baseUrl: string;\n  outputDir: string;\n  contentDir: string;\n  templateDir: string;\n}\n```\n\n### `ContentFile`\n```typescript\ninterface ContentFile {\n  slug: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;        // raw content (markdown or html)\n  metadata: Record<string, unknown>;\n  date?: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n  template?: string;\n}\n```\n\n### `BuildContext`\n```typescript\ninterface BuildContext {\n  config: SiteConfig;\n  files: ContentFile[];\n  output: Map<string, string>;  // output path -> rendered content\n  assets: Map<string, Buffer>;  // output path -> binary data\n  data: Map<string, unknown>;   // shared plugin data store\n}\n```\nThe `data` map is the inter-plugin communication mechanism. Plugins store data here (e.g., `taxonomy-tags`, `asset-manifest`, `dev-server-config`) that downstream plugins read.\n\n### `PluginHooks`\n```typescript\ninterface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n```\nThree lifecycle hooks:\n- **`beforeBuild`** -- runs once before any content transformation. Receives the full context. Used by taxonomy to build tag indices.\n- **`transformContent`** -- runs per-file. Must return a (possibly transformed) `ContentFile`. Used by markdown-ext, asset-pipeline, syntax-highlight.\n- **`afterBuild`** -- runs once after template rendering. Used by rss-feed, search-index, sitemap, dev-server to generate output artifacts.\n\n### `Plugin`\n```typescript\ninterface Plugin {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  dependencies: string[];  // names of plugins this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;\n}\n```\nEach plugin must declare its `name`, `version`, and `dependencies` (array of other plugin names). The engine uses `dependencies` for topological sorting.\n\n### `Template`\n```typescript\ninterface Template {\n  name: string;\n  render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. Build Engine (`/workspace/src/core/engine.ts`)\n\nThe `BuildEngine` class is the heart of the system.\n\n### State\n- `private plugins: Plugin[]` -- registered plugins\n- `private templates: Map<string, Template>` -- registered templates\n- `constructor(private config: SiteConfig)` -- takes site config\n\n### Registration\n- `registerPlugin(plugin)` -- pushes to the array\n- `registerTemplate(template)` -- adds to the template map by name\n\n### `resolvePluginOrder(): Plugin[]` -- Topological Sort (DAG)\nUses a DFS-based topological sort:\n1. Builds a `pluginMap` (name -> plugin)\n2. Traverses each plugin, recursing into its dependencies first\n3. Uses a `visiting` set to detect **circular dependencies** (throws `\"Circular dependency detected: {name}\"`)\n4. Checks that every dependency exists (throws `\"Missing dependency: {name} requires {dep}\"`)\n5. Returns `sorted` array in dependency-first order\n\n### `build(files: ContentFile[]): Promise<BuildContext>`\nExecution order:\n1. Creates a fresh `BuildContext` with copies of files and empty `output`/`assets`/`data` maps\n2. Calls `resolvePluginOrder()` to get the DAG-sorted plugin list\n3. **Phase 1 -- `beforeBuild` hooks**: Iterates ordered plugins sequentially, calling `beforeBuild(ctx)` on each\n4. **Phase 2 -- `transformContent` hooks**: For each plugin in order, applies its `transformContent` to **every file** in `ctx.files`, replacing the entire file list with transformed results\n5. **Phase 3 -- Template rendering**: For each file, looks up `file.template` (defaults to `'default'`), finds the template, calls `template.render(file.content, {...})`. The data object passed to render includes: `title`, `slug`, `date`, `tags`, all `metadata` entries, `siteTitle`, and `baseUrl`. Output is stored in `ctx.output` as `\"{slug}.html\"`. If no matching template exists, raw content is stored.\n6. **Phase 4 -- `afterBuild` hooks**: Iterates ordered plugins sequentially, calling `afterBuild(ctx)` on each\n7. Returns the complete `BuildContext`\n\n### Accessors\n- `getPlugins()` -- returns a copy of the plugins array\n- `getTemplates()` -- returns a copy of the templates map\n\n---\n\n## 3. Template System (`/workspace/src/core/templates.ts`)\n\nTwo factory functions:\n\n### `createDefaultTemplate()`\nName: `'default'`. Renders a full HTML page with `<!DOCTYPE html>`, `<head>` with charset and title (`{title} | {siteTitle}`), `<body>` with an `<article>` containing `<h1>`, optional `<time>` (if `data.date` is present), and `<div class=\"content\">` wrapping the content.\n\n### `createListTemplate()`\nName: `'list'`. Similar structure but uses `<div class=\"list\">` instead of `<article>`, no `<time>` element, no article wrapper.\n\n### Barrel Export (`/workspace/src/core/index.ts`)\nRe-exports `BuildEngine`, `createDefaultTemplate`, `createListTemplate`, and all types.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Core Tests (`/workspace/tests/core.test.ts`) -- 15 Tests\n\n| # | Test Name | What It Verifies |\n|---|-----------|-----------------|\n| 1 | registers plugins | `getPlugins()` returns registered plugin |\n| 2 | registers templates | `getTemplates()` has the template |\n| 3 | builds with default template and renders HTML | Output contains DOCTYPE, title, content, site title |\n| 4 | builds with list template and renders list HTML | Output uses `<div class=\"list\">` |\n| 5 | outputs raw content when no matching template | Falls back to raw content |\n| 6 | calls plugin beforeBuild hook | Hook is invoked |\n| 7 | calls plugin transformContent hook to transform files | Content is uppercased |\n| 8 | calls plugin afterBuild hook | Hook is invoked |\n| 9 | executes plugins in dependency order | `b` depends on `a`, order is `[a, b]` |\n| 10 | throws on circular dependency | `a <-> b` throws |\n| 11 | throws on missing dependency | Depends on `missing` throws |\n| 12 | applies multiple plugins transformContent in order | Content is `\"start [first] [second]\"` |\n| 13 | provides shared data store in build context | `ctx.data.set/get` works |\n| 14 | retains file metadata through build | metadata, date, tags survive |\n| 15 | produces empty output for empty file list | 0 output, 0 files |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Plugin Test Files -- Complete Analysis\n\n### 5.1 `markdown-ext.test.ts` (8 tests)\n**Import**: `createMarkdownExtPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/markdown-ext.js`\n**Hook used**: `transformContent`\n\n| Test | Expected Behavior |\n|------|------------------|\n| converts basic markdown to HTML | `# Hello` and `**bold**` produce `<h1>`, `<strong>bold</strong>` |\n| handles footnotes with `[^1]` syntax | `text[^1]... [^1]: footnote` produces `<sup><a href=\"#fn-1\">1</a></sup>` |\n| renders footnote section at bottom | Multiple footnotes produce `<section class=\"footnotes\">` with `<li id=\"fn-1\">First note.</li>` and `<li id=\"fn-2\">Second note.</li>` |\n| converts `:::note` container | `:::note\\ncontent\\n:::` produces `<div class=\"admonition admonition-note\">` |\n| converts `:::warning` container | Same pattern, class `admonition-warning` |\n| converts `:::tip` container | Same pattern, class `admonition-tip` |\n| preserves existing HTML | `<div class=\"custom\">` passes through |\n| handles empty content | Returns defined content |\n\n### 5.2 `asset-pipeline.test.ts` (8 tests)\n**Import**: `createAssetPipelinePlugin` from `../../src/plugins/asset-pipeline.js`\n**Hook used**: `transformContent`\n\n| Test | Expected Behavior |\n|------|------------------|\n| rewrites relative image URLs | `src=\"./image.png\"` becomes `src=\"/assets/image.png\"` |\n| rewrites relative link URLs | `href=\"./doc.pdf\"` becomes `href=\"/assets/doc.pdf\"` |\n| leaves absolute URLs unchanged | `https://...` untouched |\n| generates asset manifest in ctx.data | `ctx.data.get('asset-manifest')` has `{ assets: ['photo.jpg'] }` |\n| handles files with no asset references | Content unchanged |\n| handles multiple assets in one file | All three assets in manifest |\n| asset manifest includes all discovered assets | Across multiple files, manifest accumulates (length 2) |\n| does not double-process already-rewritten URLs | `/assets/image.png` stays, no manifest entry |\n\n### 5.3 `syntax-highlight.test.ts` (8 tests)\n**Import**: `createSyntaxHighlightPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/syntax-highlight.js`\n**Hook used**: `transformContent`\n\n| Test | Expected Behavior |\n|------|------------------|\n| adds language class to code blocks | `class=\"language-javascript\"` becomes `class=\"language-javascript highlighted\"` |\n| adds data-language attribute to pre tags | `<pre>` gets `data-language=\"python\"` |\n| handles multiple code blocks | Both `data-language=\"js\"` and `data-language=\"py\"` present |\n| handles code block with no language specified | `<pre><code>plain</code></pre>` unchanged, no `highlighted` class |\n| adds highlighted class to processed blocks | `language-rust` gets `highlighted` |\n| preserves code block content | `const x: number = 42;` still present |\n| handles empty code blocks | `data-language=\"js\"` and `highlighted` still added |\n| does not modify inline code | `<code>console.log()</code>` (not in `<pre>`) unchanged |\n\n### 5.4 `taxonomy.test.ts` (8 tests)\n**Import**: `createTaxonomyPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/taxonomy.js`\n**Hooks used**: `beforeBuild` and `afterBuild`\n\n| Test | Expected Behavior |\n|------|------------------|\n| builds tag index from file tags | `ctx.data.get('taxonomy-tags')` is a `Map<string, ContentFile[]>`, javascript has 2 entries, node has 1 |\n| generates tag listing pages | `ctx.output.has('tags/javascript.html')` and it contains the post title |\n| handles files with no tags | tagMap size is 0 |\n| handles files with multiple tags | 3 tags mapped correctly |\n| tag pages list all files with that tag | Both post titles appear in the tag page |\n| stores tag map in ctx.data | `ctx.data.has('taxonomy-tags')` is true |\n| handles empty file list | tagMap size 0, no errors |\n| tags are case-normalized to lowercase | `JavaScript` and `JAVASCRIPT` both become `javascript`, merged to 2 entries |\n\n### 5.5 `rss-feed.test.ts` (7 tests)\n**Import**: `createRssFeedPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/rss-feed.js`\n**Hook used**: `afterBuild`\n**Dependencies** (from TASK.md): `markdown-ext`, `taxonomy`\n\n| Test | Expected Behavior |\n|------|------------------|\n| generates valid RSS 2.0 XML | Output at `feed.xml` contains `<?xml version=\"1.0\"`, `<rss version=\"2.0\">`, `<channel>`, `<item>`, `</rss>` |\n| feed items contain HTML content not raw markdown | Content wrapped in `<![CDATA[<p>This is <strong>HTML</strong> content</p>]]>` |\n| feed items include category tags from taxonomy | Reads `taxonomy-tags` from `ctx.data`, produces `<category>javascript</category>` |\n| feed includes channel title from config | `<title>Test Site</title>` |\n| feed items sorted by date newest first | New > Mid > Old ordering in the XML |\n| handles files without dates | No `<pubDate>undefined</pubDate>` in output |\n| feed link uses baseUrl from config | `<link>https://example.com</link>` (channel) and `<link>https://example.com/post-1.html</link>` (item) |\n\n### 5.6 `search-index.test.ts` (7 tests)\n**Import**: `createSearchIndexPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/search-index.js`\n**Hook used**: `afterBuild`\n**Dependencies** (from TASK.md): `markdown-ext`, `syntax-highlight`\n\n| Test | Expected Behavior |\n|------|------------------|\n| generates search-index.json in ctx.output | `ctx.output.has('search-index.json')` |\n| index entries have title, slug, and plain text content | JSON entries with `slug`, `title`, `content` (HTML stripped: `\"Some text here\"`) |\n| HTML tags stripped from indexed content | No `<` or `>` in content, `bold` and `text` present |\n| code blocks included in searchable text | `const x = 1;` appears in plain text |\n| handles empty file list | Output is `[]` |\n| search index is valid JSON | Parses without error, is array, length 2 |\n| index entries include tags if present | `tags: ['js', 'web']` in the entry |\n\n### 5.7 `sitemap.test.ts` (7 tests)\n**Import**: `createSitemapPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/sitemap.js`\n**Hook used**: `afterBuild`\n**Dependencies** (from TASK.md): `taxonomy`, `rss-feed`\n\n| Test | Expected Behavior |\n|------|------------------|\n| generates sitemap.xml in ctx.output | `ctx.output.has('sitemap.xml')` |\n| includes all content page URLs | Both `https://example.com/post-1.html` and `post-2.html` present |\n| includes taxonomy tag page URLs | `https://example.com/tags/javascript.html` present |\n| includes feed.xml URL | `https://example.com/feed.xml` present |\n| URLs use baseUrl from config | Correct base URL |\n| sitemap is valid XML structure | Contains `<?xml version=\"1.0\"`, `<urlset`, `</urlset>`, `<url>`, `<loc>` |\n| handles site with no tag pages | No `/tags/` in output |\n\n### 5.8 `dev-server.test.ts` (7 tests)\n**Import**: `createDevServerPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/dev-server.js`\n**Hook used**: `afterBuild`\n**Dependencies** (from TASK.md): `asset-pipeline`, `search-index`\n**Note**: Test file defines a local `DevServerConfig` interface:\n```typescript\ninterface DevServerConfig {\n  port: number;\n  routes: Array<{ path: string; handler: string }>;\n  assetPaths: string[];\n  searchIndexPath: string;\n}\n```\n\n| Test | Expected Behavior |\n|------|------------------|\n| stores dev-server-config in ctx.data | `ctx.data.has('dev-server-config')` |\n| config includes port setting | `config.port` is a number |\n| config includes asset routes from asset-pipeline | Reads `asset-manifest` from `ctx.data`, populates `assetPaths` and creates routes with `handler: 'asset'` (at least 2) |\n| config includes search index path | `config.searchIndexPath` is `'/search-index.json'` |\n| config includes content routes | For each `.html` output, creates a route with `handler: 'static'` (count matches) |\n| default port is 3000 | `config.port === 3000` |\n| handles missing asset-pipeline data gracefully | `config.assetPaths` is `[]` |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Configuration Files\n\n### `package.json`\n- **Name**: `bench-ssg-toolkit`\n- **Type**: `module` (ESM)\n- **Scripts**: `build` (tsc), `lint` (eslint), `test` (vitest run)\n- **Dependencies**: `express` (5.2.1), `marked` (17.0.2), `@types/express`, `@types/marked`\n- **Dev Dependencies**: `typescript` (5.9.3), `vitest` (2.1.9), `eslint` + `@typescript-eslint` plugins\n\n### `tsconfig.json`\n- **strict**: true\n- **target**: ES2022\n- **module**: Node16\n- **moduleResolution**: Node16\n- **outDir**: `./dist`\n- **rootDir**: `./src`\n- **declaration**: true\n- **include**: `src/**/*`\n\n### `vitest.config.ts`\n- **globals**: true\n- **testTimeout**: 10000ms\n\n### `.eslintrc.cjs`\n- Uses `@typescript-eslint/parser` and recommended rules\n- Allows unused vars with `_` prefix (`argsIgnorePattern: '^_'`)\n\n---\n\n## 7. Plugin Dependency Graph (from TASK.md)\n\n```\nWave 1 (no dependencies):\n  markdown-ext        []\n  asset-pipeline      []\n  syntax-highlight    []\n  taxonomy            []\n\nWave 2:\n  rss-feed            [markdown-ext, taxonomy]\n  search-index        [markdown-ext, syntax-highlight]\n\nWave 3:\n  sitemap             [taxonomy, rss-feed]\n  dev-server          [asset-pipeline, search-index]\n```\n\nEach plugin must export a factory function named `createXxxPlugin()` (e.g., `createMarkdownExtPlugin`, `createAssetPipelinePlugin`, etc.) that returns a `Plugin` object conforming to the interface. All plugins go into `/workspace/src/plugins/`. The `marked` library (v17) is available as a dependency for markdown processing."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a4cd7be (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 36335\ntool_uses: 20\nduration_ms: 110506</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a2e1c65c-b858-4fc9-9632-74bb2bca2dd6","uuid":"c958c0ba-0ce6-4d29-bd81-be36b9010e47","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughly explore this SSG toolkit codebase. I need to understand:\n1. The full project structure (all directories and files)\n2. The Plugin interface from src/core/types.ts - every detail\n3. The build engine in src/core/ - how plugins are loaded and executed\n4. The template system\n5. All existing tests in tests/core.test.ts\n6. All plugin test files in tests/plugins/ - read every single one completely\n7. package.json for dependencies and scripts\n8. tsconfig.json for TypeScript config\n\nRead EVERY file completely. This is critical for understanding what the plugins need to do.","agentId":"a4cd7be","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have now read every single file in the codebase. Here is the complete analysis.\n\n---\n\n## Full Project Structure\n\n```\n/workspace/\n  .eslintrc.cjs                          # ESLint config\n  .gitignore                             # ignores node_modules/ and dist/\n  TASK.md                                # Task description\n  package.json                           # Project metadata and dependencies\n  package-lock.json                      # Lock file\n  tsconfig.json                          # TypeScript config\n  vitest.config.ts                       # Vitest config\n  src/\n    core/\n      index.ts                           # Barrel re-exports\n      types.ts                           # All interfaces (Plugin, BuildContext, etc.)\n      engine.ts                          # BuildEngine class with DAG plugin system\n      templates.ts                       # Default and List template factories\n    plugins/\n      .gitkeep                           # Empty placeholder directory\n  tests/\n    core.test.ts                         # 15 tests for core engine\n    plugins/\n      markdown-ext.test.ts               # 8 tests\n      asset-pipeline.test.ts             # 8 tests\n      syntax-highlight.test.ts           # 8 tests (but note: 7 \"it\" blocks -- I'll detail below)\n      taxonomy.test.ts                   # 8 tests\n      rss-feed.test.ts                   # 7 tests\n      search-index.test.ts              # 7 tests\n      sitemap.test.ts                    # 7 tests\n      dev-server.test.ts                 # 7 tests\n```\n\n---\n\n## 1. The Plugin Interface (`/workspace/src/core/types.ts`)\n\nThere are 6 interfaces defined:\n\n### `SiteConfig`\n```typescript\ninterface SiteConfig {\n  title: string;\n  baseUrl: string;\n  outputDir: string;\n  contentDir: string;\n  templateDir: string;\n}\n```\n\n### `ContentFile`\n```typescript\ninterface ContentFile {\n  slug: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;        // raw content (markdown or html)\n  metadata: Record<string, unknown>;\n  date?: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n  template?: string;\n}\n```\n\n### `BuildContext`\n```typescript\ninterface BuildContext {\n  config: SiteConfig;\n  files: ContentFile[];\n  output: Map<string, string>;  // output path -> rendered content\n  assets: Map<string, Buffer>;  // output path -> binary data\n  data: Map<string, unknown>;   // shared plugin data store\n}\n```\nThe `data` map is the inter-plugin communication mechanism. Plugins store data here (e.g., `taxonomy-tags`, `asset-manifest`, `dev-server-config`) that downstream plugins read.\n\n### `PluginHooks`\n```typescript\ninterface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n```\nThree lifecycle hooks:\n- **`beforeBuild`** -- runs once before any content transformation. Receives the full context. Used by taxonomy to build tag indices.\n- **`transformContent`** -- runs per-file. Must return a (possibly transformed) `ContentFile`. Used by markdown-ext, asset-pipeline, syntax-highlight.\n- **`afterBuild`** -- runs once after template rendering. Used by rss-feed, search-index, sitemap, dev-server to generate output artifacts.\n\n### `Plugin`\n```typescript\ninterface Plugin {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  dependencies: string[];  // names of plugins this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;\n}\n```\nEach plugin must declare its `name`, `version`, and `dependencies` (array of other plugin names). The engine uses `dependencies` for topological sorting.\n\n### `Template`\n```typescript\ninterface Template {\n  name: string;\n  render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. Build Engine (`/workspace/src/core/engine.ts`)\n\nThe `BuildEngine` class is the heart of the system.\n\n### State\n- `private plugins: Plugin[]` -- registered plugins\n- `private templates: Map<string, Template>` -- registered templates\n- `constructor(private config: SiteConfig)` -- takes site config\n\n### Registration\n- `registerPlugin(plugin)` -- pushes to the array\n- `registerTemplate(template)` -- adds to the template map by name\n\n### `resolvePluginOrder(): Plugin[]` -- Topological Sort (DAG)\nUses a DFS-based topological sort:\n1. Builds a `pluginMap` (name -> plugin)\n2. Traverses each plugin, recursing into its dependencies first\n3. Uses a `visiting` set to detect **circular dependencies** (throws `\"Circular dependency detected: {name}\"`)\n4. Checks that every dependency exists (throws `\"Missing dependency: {name} requires {dep}\"`)\n5. Returns `sorted` array in dependency-first order\n\n### `build(files: ContentFile[]): Promise<BuildContext>`\nExecution order:\n1. Creates a fresh `BuildContext` with copies of files and empty `output`/`assets`/`data` maps\n2. Calls `resolvePluginOrder()` to get the DAG-sorted plugin list\n3. **Phase 1 -- `beforeBuild` hooks**: Iterates ordered plugins sequentially, calling `beforeBuild(ctx)` on each\n4. **Phase 2 -- `transformContent` hooks**: For each plugin in order, applies its `transformContent` to **every file** in `ctx.files`, replacing the entire file list with transformed results\n5. **Phase 3 -- Template rendering**: For each file, looks up `file.template` (defaults to `'default'`), finds the template, calls `template.render(file.content, {...})`. The data object passed to render includes: `title`, `slug`, `date`, `tags`, all `metadata` entries, `siteTitle`, and `baseUrl`. Output is stored in `ctx.output` as `\"{slug}.html\"`. If no matching template exists, raw content is stored.\n6. **Phase 4 -- `afterBuild` hooks**: Iterates ordered plugins sequentially, calling `afterBuild(ctx)` on each\n7. Returns the complete `BuildContext`\n\n### Accessors\n- `getPlugins()` -- returns a copy of the plugins array\n- `getTemplates()` -- returns a copy of the templates map\n\n---\n\n## 3. Template System (`/workspace/src/core/templates.ts`)\n\nTwo factory functions:\n\n### `createDefaultTemplate()`\nName: `'default'`. Renders a full HTML page with `<!DOCTYPE html>`, `<head>` with charset and title (`{title} | {siteTitle}`), `<body>` with an `<article>` containing `<h1>`, optional `<time>` (if `data.date` is present), and `<div class=\"content\">` wrapping the content.\n\n### `createListTemplate()`\nName: `'list'`. Similar structure but uses `<div class=\"list\">` instead of `<article>`, no `<time>` element, no article wrapper.\n\n### Barrel Export (`/workspace/src/core/index.ts`)\nRe-exports `BuildEngine`, `createDefaultTemplate`, `createListTemplate`, and all types.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Core Tests (`/workspace/tests/core.test.ts`) -- 15 Tests\n\n| # | Test Name | What It Verifies |\n|---|-----------|-----------------|\n| 1 | registers plugins | `getPlugins()` returns registered plugin |\n| 2 | registers templates | `getTemplates()` has the template |\n| 3 | builds with default template and renders HTML | Output contains DOCTYPE, title, content, site title |\n| 4 | builds with list template and renders list HTML | Output uses `<div class=\"list\">` |\n| 5 | outputs raw content when no matching template | Falls back to raw content |\n| 6 | calls plugin beforeBuild hook | Hook is invoked |\n| 7 | calls plugin transformContent hook to transform files | Content is uppercased |\n| 8 | calls plugin afterBuild hook | Hook is invoked |\n| 9 | executes plugins in dependency order | `b` depends on `a`, order is `[a, b]` |\n| 10 | throws on circular dependency | `a <-> b` throws |\n| 11 | throws on missing dependency | Depends on `missing` throws |\n| 12 | applies multiple plugins transformContent in order | Content is `\"start [first] [second]\"` |\n| 13 | provides shared data store in build context | `ctx.data.set/get` works |\n| 14 | retains file metadata through build | metadata, date, tags survive |\n| 15 | produces empty output for empty file list | 0 output, 0 files |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Plugin Test Files -- Complete Analysis\n\n### 5.1 `markdown-ext.test.ts` (8 tests)\n**Import**: `createMarkdownExtPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/markdown-ext.js`\n**Hook used**: `transformContent`\n\n| Test | Expected Behavior |\n|------|------------------|\n| converts basic markdown to HTML | `# Hello` and `**bold**` produce `<h1>`, `<strong>bold</strong>` |\n| handles footnotes with `[^1]` syntax | `text[^1]... [^1]: footnote` produces `<sup><a href=\"#fn-1\">1</a></sup>` |\n| renders footnote section at bottom | Multiple footnotes produce `<section class=\"footnotes\">` with `<li id=\"fn-1\">First note.</li>` and `<li id=\"fn-2\">Second note.</li>` |\n| converts `:::note` container | `:::note\\ncontent\\n:::` produces `<div class=\"admonition admonition-note\">` |\n| converts `:::warning` container | Same pattern, class `admonition-warning` |\n| converts `:::tip` container | Same pattern, class `admonition-tip` |\n| preserves existing HTML | `<div class=\"custom\">` passes through |\n| handles empty content | Returns defined content |\n\n### 5.2 `asset-pipeline.test.ts` (8 tests)\n**Import**: `createAssetPipelinePlugin` from `../../src/plugins/asset-pipeline.js`\n**Hook used**: `transformContent`\n\n| Test | Expected Behavior |\n|------|------------------|\n| rewrites relative image URLs | `src=\"./image.png\"` becomes `src=\"/assets/image.png\"` |\n| rewrites relative link URLs | `href=\"./doc.pdf\"` becomes `href=\"/assets/doc.pdf\"` |\n| leaves absolute URLs unchanged | `https://...` untouched |\n| generates asset manifest in ctx.data | `ctx.data.get('asset-manifest')` has `{ assets: ['photo.jpg'] }` |\n| handles files with no asset references | Content unchanged |\n| handles multiple assets in one file | All three assets in manifest |\n| asset manifest includes all discovered assets | Across multiple files, manifest accumulates (length 2) |\n| does not double-process already-rewritten URLs | `/assets/image.png` stays, no manifest entry |\n\n### 5.3 `syntax-highlight.test.ts` (8 tests)\n**Import**: `createSyntaxHighlightPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/syntax-highlight.js`\n**Hook used**: `transformContent`\n\n| Test | Expected Behavior |\n|------|------------------|\n| adds language class to code blocks | `class=\"language-javascript\"` becomes `class=\"language-javascript highlighted\"` |\n| adds data-language attribute to pre tags | `<pre>` gets `data-language=\"python\"` |\n| handles multiple code blocks | Both `data-language=\"js\"` and `data-language=\"py\"` present |\n| handles code block with no language specified | `<pre><code>plain</code></pre>` unchanged, no `highlighted` class |\n| adds highlighted class to processed blocks | `language-rust` gets `highlighted` |\n| preserves code block content | `const x: number = 42;` still present |\n| handles empty code blocks | `data-language=\"js\"` and `highlighted` still added |\n| does not modify inline code | `<code>console.log()</code>` (not in `<pre>`) unchanged |\n\n### 5.4 `taxonomy.test.ts` (8 tests)\n**Import**: `createTaxonomyPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/taxonomy.js`\n**Hooks used**: `beforeBuild` and `afterBuild`\n\n| Test | Expected Behavior |\n|------|------------------|\n| builds tag index from file tags | `ctx.data.get('taxonomy-tags')` is a `Map<string, ContentFile[]>`, javascript has 2 entries, node has 1 |\n| generates tag listing pages | `ctx.output.has('tags/javascript.html')` and it contains the post title |\n| handles files with no tags | tagMap size is 0 |\n| handles files with multiple tags | 3 tags mapped correctly |\n| tag pages list all files with that tag | Both post titles appear in the tag page |\n| stores tag map in ctx.data | `ctx.data.has('taxonomy-tags')` is true |\n| handles empty file list | tagMap size 0, no errors |\n| tags are case-normalized to lowercase | `JavaScript` and `JAVASCRIPT` both become `javascript`, merged to 2 entries |\n\n### 5.5 `rss-feed.test.ts` (7 tests)\n**Import**: `createRssFeedPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/rss-feed.js`\n**Hook used**: `afterBuild`\n**Dependencies** (from TASK.md): `markdown-ext`, `taxonomy`\n\n| Test | Expected Behavior |\n|------|------------------|\n| generates valid RSS 2.0 XML | Output at `feed.xml` contains `<?xml version=\"1.0\"`, `<rss version=\"2.0\">`, `<channel>`, `<item>`, `</rss>` |\n| feed items contain HTML content not raw markdown | Content wrapped in `<![CDATA[<p>This is <strong>HTML</strong> content</p>]]>` |\n| feed items include category tags from taxonomy | Reads `taxonomy-tags` from `ctx.data`, produces `<category>javascript</category>` |\n| feed includes channel title from config | `<title>Test Site</title>` |\n| feed items sorted by date newest first | New > Mid > Old ordering in the XML |\n| handles files without dates | No `<pubDate>undefined</pubDate>` in output |\n| feed link uses baseUrl from config | `<link>https://example.com</link>` (channel) and `<link>https://example.com/post-1.html</link>` (item) |\n\n### 5.6 `search-index.test.ts` (7 tests)\n**Import**: `createSearchIndexPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/search-index.js`\n**Hook used**: `afterBuild`\n**Dependencies** (from TASK.md): `markdown-ext`, `syntax-highlight`\n\n| Test | Expected Behavior |\n|------|------------------|\n| generates search-index.json in ctx.output | `ctx.output.has('search-index.json')` |\n| index entries have title, slug, and plain text content | JSON entries with `slug`, `title`, `content` (HTML stripped: `\"Some text here\"`) |\n| HTML tags stripped from indexed content | No `<` or `>` in content, `bold` and `text` present |\n| code blocks included in searchable text | `const x = 1;` appears in plain text |\n| handles empty file list | Output is `[]` |\n| search index is valid JSON | Parses without error, is array, length 2 |\n| index entries include tags if present | `tags: ['js', 'web']` in the entry |\n\n### 5.7 `sitemap.test.ts` (7 tests)\n**Import**: `createSitemapPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/sitemap.js`\n**Hook used**: `afterBuild`\n**Dependencies** (from TASK.md): `taxonomy`, `rss-feed`\n\n| Test | Expected Behavior |\n|------|------------------|\n| generates sitemap.xml in ctx.output | `ctx.output.has('sitemap.xml')` |\n| includes all content page URLs | Both `https://example.com/post-1.html` and `post-2.html` present |\n| includes taxonomy tag page URLs | `https://example.com/tags/javascript.html` present |\n| includes feed.xml URL | `https://example.com/feed.xml` present |\n| URLs use baseUrl from config | Correct base URL |\n| sitemap is valid XML structure | Contains `<?xml version=\"1.0\"`, `<urlset`, `</urlset>`, `<url>`, `<loc>` |\n| handles site with no tag pages | No `/tags/` in output |\n\n### 5.8 `dev-server.test.ts` (7 tests)\n**Import**: `createDevServerPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/dev-server.js`\n**Hook used**: `afterBuild`\n**Dependencies** (from TASK.md): `asset-pipeline`, `search-index`\n**Note**: Test file defines a local `DevServerConfig` interface:\n```typescript\ninterface DevServerConfig {\n  port: number;\n  routes: Array<{ path: string; handler: string }>;\n  assetPaths: string[];\n  searchIndexPath: string;\n}\n```\n\n| Test | Expected Behavior |\n|------|------------------|\n| stores dev-server-config in ctx.data | `ctx.data.has('dev-server-config')` |\n| config includes port setting | `config.port` is a number |\n| config includes asset routes from asset-pipeline | Reads `asset-manifest` from `ctx.data`, populates `assetPaths` and creates routes with `handler: 'asset'` (at least 2) |\n| config includes search index path | `config.searchIndexPath` is `'/search-index.json'` |\n| config includes content routes | For each `.html` output, creates a route with `handler: 'static'` (count matches) |\n| default port is 3000 | `config.port === 3000` |\n| handles missing asset-pipeline data gracefully | `config.assetPaths` is `[]` |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Configuration Files\n\n### `package.json`\n- **Name**: `bench-ssg-toolkit`\n- **Type**: `module` (ESM)\n- **Scripts**: `build` (tsc), `lint` (eslint), `test` (vitest run)\n- **Dependencies**: `express` (5.2.1), `marked` (17.0.2), `@types/express`, `@types/marked`\n- **Dev Dependencies**: `typescript` (5.9.3), `vitest` (2.1.9), `eslint` + `@typescript-eslint` plugins\n\n### `tsconfig.json`\n- **strict**: true\n- **target**: ES2022\n- **module**: Node16\n- **moduleResolution**: Node16\n- **outDir**: `./dist`\n- **rootDir**: `./src`\n- **declaration**: true\n- **include**: `src/**/*`\n\n### `vitest.config.ts`\n- **globals**: true\n- **testTimeout**: 10000ms\n\n### `.eslintrc.cjs`\n- Uses `@typescript-eslint/parser` and recommended rules\n- Allows unused vars with `_` prefix (`argsIgnorePattern: '^_'`)\n\n---\n\n## 7. Plugin Dependency Graph (from TASK.md)\n\n```\nWave 1 (no dependencies):\n  markdown-ext        []\n  asset-pipeline      []\n  syntax-highlight    []\n  taxonomy            []\n\nWave 2:\n  rss-feed            [markdown-ext, taxonomy]\n  search-index        [markdown-ext, syntax-highlight]\n\nWave 3:\n  sitemap             [taxonomy, rss-feed]\n  dev-server          [asset-pipeline, search-index]\n```\n\nEach plugin must export a factory function named `createXxxPlugin()` (e.g., `createMarkdownExtPlugin`, `createAssetPipelinePlugin`, etc.) that returns a `Plugin` object conforming to the interface. All plugin